List in Java:-
    A List in Java is a collection that stores multiple elements in order.
    It is part of the Java Collection Framework and allows duplicate elements. 📋
    
    The List interface is in the package:
          
        java.util

    Common classes that implement List:

        ArrayList
        LinkedList
        Vector

1️⃣ Creating a List
    Example using ArrayList:
          import java.util.*;

          class Test {
              public static void main(String[] args) {
          
                  List<Integer> numbers = new ArrayList<>();
          
                  numbers.add(10);
                  numbers.add(20);
                  numbers.add(30);
          
                  System.out.println(numbers);
              }
          }

2️⃣ Important List Methods
        Method	Description
        add()	Adds an element
        remove()	Removes an element
        get()	Gets element at index
        set()	Updates element
        size()	Returns number of elements

3️⃣ Example Using List Methods
        import java.util.*;
        
        class Test {
            public static void main(String[] args) {
        
                List<String> fruits = new ArrayList<>();
        
                fruits.add("Apple");
                fruits.add("Mango");
                fruits.add("Banana");
        
                System.out.println(fruits.get(1));
                System.out.println(fruits.size());
            }
        }
